nt to double-check the prices you set, you can hit the List Items button and it will show you the items and the prices you have set.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;How can I sell/buy bags?: There is a new NPC named Caerlyna, she is a Barb outside the middle building, near the Nexus bank. You can give a weight reducing bag to her (like a handmade backpack or one that you have looted) and she will give you a Token. Bags cannot go into trader satchels but tokens can. If you want to buy a bag, search on the word Token. To get a bag from a token, just take the token to Caerlyna and give it to her. Make sure you have an open slot for a bag. Caerlyna costs nothing and you don't even have to talk to her, just hand her bags or tokens.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;What do I do now?: Best thing is to walk away from your computer and do other things for awhile -- like a couple hours, give it some time. While in trader mode you have basically turned into an NPC. You can talk through /tells or /ooc or /auction but you can't move, you can't cast spells. You don't need to be there to sell things. If your items aren't selling there are a couple of possibilities. One is that there is no demand for the item (such as a low quality lion skin that isn't used for anything and should be sold to a NPC vendor), or perhaps that your price is set too high, or maybe your price is fine but no one has wanted your item yet.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Hopefully you will come back to find an empty bag and money in your pockets and you are ready to play. You can hit the End Trader Button and REMEMBER to go to the Bank and put your trader satchel(s) away before leaving the bazaar.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
